gcci.text: The $3.15/hr H100 pricing reflects tight supply constraints and high capex barriers, as chip availability remains the primary bottleneck preventing scaled AI infrastructure deployment.

gtpi.text: The $1.25/1M token input pricing signals aggressive API price wars among model providers, with efficiency gains now determining competitive survival rather than raw capability.

gagl.text: The 120 TWh annual load represents critical grid strain thresholds that demand immediate nuclear adoption strategies to maintain AI infrastructure growth without carbon penalties.

aipi.text: Current AI infrastructure valuations show bubble characteristics with unsustainable growth rates, as capital efficiency metrics lag behind deployment pace, creating systemic risk exposure.
